          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Consolidate your debt\nThanks to lower interest rates, refinancing can free up cash to help you pay off other debts or expenses you may have. If you refinance your existing mortgage, take out a new mortgage with a larger balance and withdraw the difference in cash, this is considered a \u201ccash-out refinance\u201d. You need at least 20% equity in your home for a cash-out refinance.",
