          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-3be3eb74f63d4321",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Frequently asked questions\nDoes CIBC have a mortgage calculator?\nYes, find out how much you can afford, get pre-qualified online in just a few seconds or apply for a mortgage with CIBC\u2019s mortgage tools and calculators .\u00a0Additionally, CIBC has a home equity calculator that can help you find out how much you may qualify to borrow through a mortgage or line of credit.\nWhat is home equity?\nYour home equity is the value of your home, minus total outstanding debt \u2014 such as mortgages and liens \u2014 secured against your property. You can calculate your home equity as follows: Property value \u2013 total debt secured by the property = home equity Example: If your property is worth $500,000 and the mortgage is $400,000, your home equity is $100,000 ($500,000 - $400,000 = $100,000). Your home equity increases as the debt secured by the property decreases. Estimate your available equity and find out how",
