          "evidence_text_excerpt": "How does the mortgage stress test work?\ntest work?\nThe federal mortgage stress test is a regulatory measure in Canada that gauges your ability to pay your mortgage if your interest rate or payment amount ever increased.\nThe test requires you to qualify for whichever rate is higher: either a Mortgage Qualifying Rate (MQR) of 5.25% or your actual contract rate at the time of switch plus 2.0%.\n5.25%\nswitch plus 2.0%.\nIf you're switching your mortgage from one federally-regulated financial institution to another without increasing the loan amount 4 or changing the amortization, you won't need to go through the mortgage stress test. Instead, you'll only need to qualify at the new rate offered to you (the contract rate).",
