        {
          "field_name": "product_name",
          "candidate_value": "Debt consolidation mortgage",
          "value_type": "string",
          "confidence": 0.97,
          "extraction_method": "openai_dynamic_extractor",
          "source_document_id": "src-cibc-html-081d40a1b1037fe2",
          "source_snapshot_id": "snap-fb18c06d3450abc0",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-f73d525eec4b3ab8",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Consolidate your debt into one easy payment\nHigh-interest debt from credit cards or loans makes it hard to manage your finances. But if you're a homeowner,\u00a0you can\u00a0take advantage of your home's equity. Combine\u00a0the money you owe into a debt consolidation mortgage (also known as a conventional mortgage Opens a popup. ), home equity loan or line of credit.\nOpens a popup.",
          "anchor_type": "section",
          "anchor_value": "consolidate-your-debt-into-one-easy-payment",
          "page_no": null,
          "chunk_index": 1,
          "field_metadata": {
            "dynamic_product_type": true
          }
        },
        {
          "field_name": "description_short",
          "candidate_value": "A long-term mortgage that combines multiple debts into one loan and payment, potentially using home equity through refinancing.",
          "value_type": "string",
          "confidence": 0.95,
          "extraction_method": "openai_dynamic_extractor",
          "source_document_id": "src-cibc-html-081d40a1b1037fe2",
          "source_snapshot_id": "snap-fb18c06d3450abc0",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-e49d702a642e81f0",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "What's debt consolidation?\nDebt consolidation is debt financing that combines 2 or more loans into one. A debt consolidation mortgage is a long-term loan that gives you the funds to pay off several debts at the same time. Once your other debts are paid off, it leaves you with just one loan to pay, rather than several.\nTo consolidate your debt, ask your lender for a loan equivalent to or beyond the total amount you owe. Consolidation is particularly useful for high-interest loans, such as credit cards. Usually, the lender settles all outstanding debt and all creditors are paid at once.\nDebt consolidation is a great way to streamline your finances.\u00a0But before you cash out your home equity Opens a popup. or refinance Opens a popup. your mortgage, learn more about managing your debt.\u00a0These 6 tips can help:\nOpens a popup.\nLook for lower interest\u00a0rates\nKnow how much the loan will cost",
          "anchor_type": "section",
          "anchor_value": "what-s-debt-consolidation",
          "page_no": null,
          "chunk_index": 2,
          "field_metadata": {
            "dynamic_product_type": true
          }
        },
        {
          "field_name": "interest_payment_frequency",
          "candidate_value": "weekly",
          "value_type": "string",
          "confidence": 0.66,
          "extraction_method": "heuristic_frequency",
          "source_document_id": "src-cibc-html-081d40a1b1037fe2",
          "source_snapshot_id": "snap-fb18c06d3450abc0",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-5b45aa74cfae8245",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Why consolidate debt into a mortgage?\nRefinancing your existing mortgage into a\u00a0consolidation loan\u00a0combines your debts\u00a0into one payment. This is a great option if you have high-interest loans and you're only paying the interest rather than the principal.\nWhen you refinance, you can get up to a maximum of 80% of the appraised\u00a0value of your home minus the remaining\u00a0mortgage.\nInterest rates on a debt consolidation mortgage might be different from your existing mortgage. If you\u00a0change your mortgage, the terms of your original agreement will likely change.\nDebt consolidation mortgages\u00a0come with a structured payment plan and an assured pay-off date.\u00a0Payment schedules vary: weekly,\u00a0biweekly,\u00a0semi-monthly\u00a0or monthly over a negotiated term.\u00a0Refinancing fees apply, such as appraisals, title search, title insurance and legal fees.",
          "anchor_type": "section",
          "anchor_value": "why-consolidate-debt-into-a-mortgage",
          "page_no": null,
          "chunk_index": 5,
          "field_metadata": {
            "retrieval_mode": "metadata-only",
            "matched_keywords": [
